    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough. but when u say a \"balance\" needs to be struck, it feels like one side is always claiming things are \"stifling\" or \"inefficient\" while the other side is just trying to survive. isnt it kind of true that without unions, companies would just keep exploits workers indefinitely? like, is there even a \"balance\" if workers have no power?",
